5395b666-5ec5-4d1d-9fdb-ed21b07c9337.16907cd2-df09-4213-8c29-822a606f905d.description=
Checks to see if a string matches a specific rule.

Inputs\:
matchType - The type of match to perform.
toMatch - The string to check if matches another string.
matchTo - The string to match against.
ignoreCase - Boolean value for whether or not to ignore case during match.

Responses\:
success - The String matched.
failure - The string did not match, or something went wrong.
5395b666-5ec5-4d1d-9fdb-ed21b07c9337.2acfa64d-78e3-4abb-af65-b6cf54f7208c.description=
Formats the event values to form a subject.

Inputs\:
xml - xml with trap information. This is the Alert XML format described in the CreateTicket flow
subject - Subject for the vantive event and can contain tokens like ${CMDBName} , ${Summary}

Outputs\:
subject - Returns a subject with the tokens replaced.

Responses\:
success - If everything went fine.
failure - If something went wrong.

5395b666-5ec5-4d1d-9fdb-ed21b07c9337.6a4b61ac-c683-4454-89c5-bfafbb11c0a6.description=
Service to perform an HTTP GET via the Java HTTP Client

Inputs\:
url - the url to attempt to retrieve.
username - the username to authenticate to url with.
password - the password for username.
timeout - a timeout after which the connection should be terminated, or 0 for no timeout.
useCookies - Enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. valid options are\: true/false
followRedirects - specifies whether or not the get command should automatically follow redirects.
trustAllRoots - enables weak security over SSL. A SSH certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it. valid options are\: true/false
proxy - a proxy to use when accessing the web site.
proxyPort - a port on the proxy to connect to.
proxyUsername - a username to use when connecting to the proxy.
proxyPassword - a password to use when connecting to the proxy.
encodeURL - perform URL encoding.

Responses\:
success - URL retrieved successfully.
failure - The url could not be retrieved.
5395b666-5ec5-4d1d-9fdb-ed21b07c9337.description=
Creates a ticket, returns success only if a ticket ID is generated by the ticketing service.

Inputs\:
alertXml- AlertXml is the event and vantive details the followingformat\:

Provided vantiveLogin
Provided vantiveUserID
...
Event CMDBName
Event Summary


ticketUrl- Ticket URL for the ticketing url service
noteAction- Its the action to take the notes field


Outputs\:
ticket- id of the ticket created

Responses\:
success - Everything worked.
failure - Something went wrong.
